      "content": "thanks for the fix. i see what you mean about the unique_ptr. i noticed in the original code that my destructor for DataBuffer was empty, so i didn't realize the internal buffer wasn't being deleted. besides smart pointers, what would be the direct way to fix the leak in my original code using just raw pointers? i need to understand the specific mechanism of the leak first.",
